### Technologies[^12]



*   TypeScript, Vue and Node.js
*   RabbitMQ, Kubernetes and PostgreSQL
*   The technologies of the web (HTTP, JSON APIs, REST, HTML)
*   SQL database programming and performance
*   *NIX environments, and Operating system details (including processes, threads and file systems)
*   Python
*   Google Cloud Platform
*   Event-driven system design and architecture

Clearbanc also employs AI and machine learning to put a valuation on startups, gathering data from a number of e-commerce integrations with [partners like Shopify, Square and Stripe.


## Landscape {#landscape}

**Domain: **B2B lending and startup capital


### Major Trends and Innovations[^13]



*   Improving the digital borrower experience[^14]


    *   Consumer (B2C) like experiences in B2B applications
    *   Faster, easier, integrated registration experience
    *   Identity management and financial authentication services
*   AI and machine learning enabled automation and efficiencies
    *   alternative credit decisioning models (ACD) that use ML.
    *   predictive and proactive models for risk management and underwriting
    *   operational efficiencies from improved data analysis and faster insights
    *   AI assistants for decision support
*   Blockchain for transaction security and identity management
*   RegTech (Regulations Technologies) to simplify complex local and international compliance standards like AML (anti-money laundering), GDPR (data privacy and storage compliance in the EU), and multi-factor authentication methods (i.e. 3D Secure protocols in Europe)


